Class ATCDirector

  • java.lang.Object
    • ptolemy.kernel.util.NamedObj

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, Executable, Initializable, SuperdenseTimeDirector, Changeable, Debuggable, DebugListener, Derivable, ModelErrorHandler, MoMLExportable, Moveable, Nameable

    public class ATCDirector
extends AbstractATCDirector
    A director for modeling air traffic control systems. This director provides a receiver that consults the destination actor to determine whether it can accept an input, and provides mechanisms for handling rejection of an input.
    Since:
    Ptolemy II 11.0
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    Maryam Bagheri
